notesStmt.note: Imperfect at the beginning and at the end.
Several folios more or less damaged.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: Midrash ha-ḥefets, a philosophical midrash on the Pentateuch by Zechariah ben Solomon-Rofe, aka Yaḥya ben Saliman.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 22 24; written lines: 22 24; Occasional marginal notes.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Two Yemenite semi-cursive scripts of 17th century.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Spine title: 'Midrash ha-Hefets. Hebrew-Arabic. Brit. Mus. Oriental 4840.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Morris, Heller & Weiss: purchased by the British Library on 14 November 1894: inscribed, folio [216v].
